{
  "local_port": 55794,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you block someone on Quora?",
  "response": "To block someone on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the User's Profile:**\n   Navigate to the profile of the user you want to block. You can do this by clicking on their name or profile picture wherever you see it on Quora (e.g., in a question, answer, or comment).\n\n2. **Access the Three-Dot Menu:**\n   On their profile, look for the three dots (\u22ef) usually located near their profile information or at the top right corner of the profile page.\n\n3. **Select \"Block\":**\n   Click on the three dots, and a menu will appear. From this menu, select the \"Block\" option.\n\n4. **Confirm the Block:**\n   A confirmation dialog will appear, asking if you're sure you want to block the user. Click \"Block\" to confirm.\n\nOnce you've blocked a user, they will not be able to follow you, mention you, or interact with your content. They also won't be able to see your content in their feeds, and any existing followers/following relationships between you and the blocked user will be removed.\n\nIf you change your mind later, you can unblock the user by going to your own profile, clicking on \"Privacy and Settings,\" then navigating to the \"Blocked Users\" section, finding the user, and clicking \"Unblock.\"",
